<i>noun</i>: 환난 [환ː난], 칼바람 [칼바람], 질곡 [질곡], 시련 [시ː련], 수난 [수난], 괴롬 [괴롬/궤롬], 고난 [고난] <br>
<ul style="list-style-type:square">
<li><i>noun</i><br>
<dt>환난 [환ː난]</dt><br>
<dd>hardship; adversity; ordeal; suffering</dd><br>
<dd>매우 걱정되고 고통스러운 일.</dd><br>
<dd>An extremely worrying and painful situation.</dd><br>
<dt>칼바람 [칼바람]</dt><br>
<dd>1. cold wind; icy blast</dd><br>
<dd>몹시 차고 매서운 바람.</dd><br>
<dd>A very cold and strong wind.</dd><br>
<dd>2. big trouble; ordeal</dd><br>
<dd>(비유적으로) 아주 심하게 괴롭히거나 해롭게 하는 일.</dd><br>
<dd>(figurative) A very severe trouble or harm.</dd><br>
<dt>질곡 [질곡]</dt><br>
<dd>1. fetters; shackles</dd><br>
<dd>죄인의 발목에 채우는 나무로 만든 형틀과 손목에 채우는 수갑.</dd><br>
<dd>Wooden shackles for encircling the ankles and wrists of a prisoner.</dd><br>
<dd>2. ordeal</dd><br>
<dd>(비유적으로) 어떤 행동을 하거나 권리를 행사할 자유가 제한되어 고통스러운 상태.</dd><br>
<dd>(figurative) A painful state in which one's freedom to do something or exercise one's rights is restricted.</dd><br>
<dt>시련 [시ː련]</dt><br>
<dd>1. hardship; ordeal</dd><br>
<dd>힘든 고난이나 고비.</dd><br>
<dd>A difficult and painful situation or crisis.</dd><br>
<dd>2. trial; test</dd><br>
<dd>의지나 사람됨을 알아보기 위해 시험하여 봄.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of testing someone to find out about his/her will or personality.</dd><br>
<dt>수난 [수난]</dt><br>
<dd>1. suffering; ordeal</dd><br>
<dd>견디기 힘든 어려운 일을 당함.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of suffering an unbearable experience.</dd><br>
<dd>2. Passion</dd><br>
<dd>기독교에서, 예수가 십자가에 못 박힐 때 당한 고난.</dd><br>
<dd>In Christianity, the suffering faced by Jesus Christ when he was crucified.</dd><br>
<dt>괴롬 [괴롬/궤롬]</dt><br>
<dd>suffering; ordeal; agony</dd><br>
<dd>몸이나 마음이 고통스러운 상태. 또는 그런 느낌.</dd><br>
<dd>The state of being in pain physically or emotionally, or this feeling.</dd><br>
<dt>고난 [고난]</dt><br>
<dd>hardship; trouble; suffering; difficulty; adversity; trial; ordeal</dd><br>
<dd>매우 괴롭고 어려움.</dd><br>
<dd>A state or situation which is extremely difficult and painful.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>